itemListElement.name: Private Half-Day Seattle Tour with Private Guide

name: Private Half-Day Seattle Tour with Private Guide
description:
This is the quintessential Seattle experience put into a four-hour intimate tour that explores the many faces of the city.

Avoid the big buses, take the private tour with a personalized service and find your own way around the city.

Seattle is a cosmopolitan city where technology, nature, and the arts meet, surrounded by snow-capped mountains and the Puget Sound, it invites you to explore the many facets of the city and its breathtaking views.

The city's vibrant culture, with theatres, opera, outstanding galleries and museums, and excellent restaurants is captivating. Yet through all this, it clings to its own unconventionality. Many of Seattle's iconic stops are included as well as some hidden gems to provide you with a real feel of this beautiful city.

I highly recommend taking this tour early on in your Seattle visit in order to benefit from all the information and directions!
At every location, we will take a brief photo stop. The tour can be scheduled as a night tour.

name: The Seattle Coffee Tour
description:
Get a true taste of Seattle's coffee scene with a local guide, as you explore the vibrant Capitol Hill neighborhood where coffee culture and counterculture intersect. Step into various coffee shops to taste a wide array of different brews, from traditional favorites to unique creations. Learn about the coffee production process, gain insight into the local culture and discover the stories behind each cup of coffee. 
Highlights
- Get your caffeine fix with three styles of coffee, from single-origin espressos to infused brews.
- Explore the coffee roasting and production process.
- Learn about Capitol Hill progressive history and longstanding counterculture.
- Get recommendations for the best bakeries, restaurants, and nightlife activities of Capitol Hill.
- This tour is carbon neutral, operated by a B Corp certified company committed to using travel as a force for good.

description: Experience the fun, excitement and beauty that is Seattle. Experience the front line of modern art and transportation as we pass the Sculpture Park and explore the City Center from Space Needle to the musical International Fountain. Enjoy lush parks and blossoming flowers as we taste and smell our way through Pike Place Market, before we glide through the rich architecture and soaring cityscapes of Downtown and the International District.

review.reviewBody: Our tour guide Woody, was amazing!!! Super kind, informative & outgoing. He was knowledge about the history & present state of Seattle. review.reviewBody: Woody was very knowledgable and helpful throughout the tour making sure street was clear of cars and making sure I could use segway. Got to know a lot of the city and hidden gems that I would have no way of finding on my own. Really fun touring on a segway. Recommend it if in Seattle will have fun.

review.name: Lots of fun
review.reviewBody: We weren't sure what to expect from a segway tour.  It turned out to be a lot of fun.  The Segways were fun to ride, the tour was really well done and we got to see a lot of the city.  Highly recommended as a way to quickly see the city.

review.name: Excellent Tour
review.reviewBody:
My thirteen year old son and I went on a fabulous two hour Segway tour with our guide Woody. We experienced impeccable service from start to finish. It began perfectly with an introduction, safety training, opportunity to practice, and a review of our tour. Woody was hospitable not only to us, but also fellow members of the community and he made certain that everyone, the community and those of us on the tour, were safe and comfortable at all times. His humor, knowledge of the city and surrounding areas, historical insights, and other personal attention to details made being a tourist in our home town one of the best days we have had in this beautiful city. I would highly recommend this tour not only for the fun and novelty of the experience, but also the learning, and ability to see so many wonderful sites within a mere two hour window of time while never feeling rushed. In addition, the photo opportunities Woody encouraged will make for lasting memories as will his recommendations for where we might go for dinner and or snacks. We are now big fans of piroshkies as well as the Seattle Segway tour.
Thank you Woody!

review.name: Great Impromptu Private Segway Tour in the Fog!

The tour ended up being a private one and Woody took me to places that he's not normally able to take folks to.  Great way to see Seattle.  It was also the first time I'd been on a Segway and he did a good job at getting me comfortable.  The fog wasn't very cooperative, but I saw a side of Seattle I would have never seen otherwise! He has good experience introducing the sites of Seattle Downtown and knew well where to shoot nice photos. He helped us shoot nice photos wherever we wanted. He even waited for us while  we stopped at Space Needle to reschedule our tour. We ran out of time a little bit, but he was still smiling.

review.name: Beautiful views of the city!
review.reviewBody:
I really enjoyed my experience parasailing!  Although I was pretty nervous that it would be scary, it actually was beautiful and relaxing.  It is the type of activity that sounds very adventurous and difficult, but as long as you know how to sit down...you will be fine.  You can do this activity in your street clothes.  You don't have to enter the water at all.  You just slowly take off from a sitting position on the back of the boat and they land you on the back of the boat in the same position.  No skills required.  You are well strapped in too.  As long as you don't have a fear of heights, I would recommend it to anyone.

On my ride, there were about 8 of us in total and each of us (in pairs) were up in the air for a about 15-20 minutes, which I think is a sufficient amount of time.  You feel like you are higher than the space needle (which you probably aren't, but that's how it feels) and it is one of the most incredible views of Elliot Bay and the Seattle skyline I could imagine.  I went on the 7pm ride and it is gorgeous as the sun is setting.  You don't feel like you are moving particularly fast, you just feel like you are floating.  The staff were friendly and willing to answer questions during the ride.

My main critiques would be that they were a little unclear about arrival instructions.  The website told us to be there at least 15 minutes before the ride, but there was no one to be seen until the exact time the ride was supposed to start and no signage to indicate I was waiting in the right place.  Also, they offer package picture deals, but those cost extra, and I thought they were a little expensive, considering the initial trip isn't that cheap.

But overall it is truly a unique experience and something that I am very glad I can say that I did.  I would recommend it!

review.name: Amazing parasailing adventure
review.reviewBody:
This was a fantastic experience from start to finish! It was easy to book our group online and we received great email instructions and a reminder a few days before our reservation.
The parasailing itself was so much fun. When we were in the air, my 10 year old son said that it was very relaxing. And I would have to agree with him. We had amazing views and a very smooth trip. Andrew and Lucas were absolutely amazing and made the experience perfect. I highly recommend parasailing with Parasail Seattle!

Even making sure that moms got great shots of their kids in the tube. Put this place and this experience on your bucket list.

mainEntity.name: How does the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience work?

acceptedAnswer.text: A vertical wind tunnel has fans at the top to draw air through the flight chamber and then push it back down the sides. The air is then compressed & sped up before it reenters the flight chamber causing a smooth column of air that enables you to fly.

mainEntity.name: How safe is the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: The unique design of the wind tunnel, with its wall-to-wall air column, along with certified and highly-trained instructors, allows you to safely enjoy your flight. Your instructor is with you the entire time regardless of your level of experience.

mainEntity.name: What is a Wind Tunnel?

acceptedAnswer.text: Very simply, a wind tunnel is a machine that moves a lot of air. A vertical wind tunnel moves air in a vertical column at speeds high enough to keep a person safely floating.

mainEntity.name: How early should I arrive for the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: It is important that you arrive on time for your scheduled session. Your experience will begin promptly upon your arrival so please plan to arrive 10-15 minutes early for your reservation so you have time to check in.

mainEntity.name: Do I fly alone or with a group during the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: Generally, a group of up to 12 guests fly in each session. Your friends and family will be part of the same group, however, you will fly one at a time in the flight chamber one-on-one with your instructor.

mainEntity.name: How long is each flight during the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: Each flight within the wind tunnel lasts 60 seconds. The entire iFLY first-time flyer experience takes approx. 1 hour and 30 minutes from start to finish.

mainEntity.name: Can I bring family/friends to watch, but not participate in the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: If someone chooses to come to watch, he or she is welcome to accompany you through your experience and can watch from the observation area.

mainEntity.name: Is it scary during the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: Generally, no. There’s no jumping, no falling, and no experience is needed. You simply float on a column of air. There is no sensation of falling or anything that would make you feel motion sickness.

mainEntity.name: Is it hard to breathe during the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: Not at all. It is the same as if you stick your head out a car window while driving. All you feel is the wind in your face. Just breathe normally, either through your mouth or your nose.

mainEntity.name: Is the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience appropriate for younger children?

acceptedAnswer.text: Flyers can be as young as 3 years of age and there is no upper age limit. Children under 18 years of age need to have a parent or guardian sign their waiver.

mainEntity.name: Are there any weight restrictions to participate in the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: Participants must weigh less than 300 pounds. Any guests who weigh between 260 and 300 pounds must notate current weight in the "Special Requirements" box at checkout to avoid delays upon arrival.

mainEntity.name: How tall do I have to be to participate in the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: There are no height restrictions to fly!

mainEntity.name: What should I wear for the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: Please wear well-fitting, lace-up sneakers, or running shoes. Wear casual clothes, preferably pants and a shirt without a collar. You will wear your flight suit on top of your clothes. Anyone with long hair should wear it braided and in a low bun.

mainEntity.name: Can I participate in the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience if I am pregnant?

acceptedAnswer.text: For safety reasons, women who are pregnant should not fly.

mainEntity.name: Do I have to do the training session to participate in the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: All first-time flyers are required to take the training class. You’ll get a lot of important and helpful information as well as some pre-flight practice of your flying position.

mainEntity.name: Can I wear my glasses during the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: Yes. There are larger goggles that fit over eyeglasses available for use.

mainEntity.name: Will I need to take off my watch and jewelry to participate in the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: You should remove any items that might flap around or become loose, such as earrings, necklaces, bracelets, watches, rings, and hair accessories. You should also empty your pockets. Lockers are available, but it's best to leave valuables at home.

mainEntity.name: Why do I need to wear a flight suit during the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: For safety - the instructors are trained to grasp the handles of your flight suit should you need spotting.

mainEntity.name: Can I do flips and tricks in the tunnel during the Seattle Indoor Skydiving Experience?

acceptedAnswer.text: The primary concern is for your safety in the flight chamber so the tricks or flips are for experienced flyers only. Some flyers are able to do turns or move around during their first flight. Ask your instructor how to advance your flight skills.
